  <body>
    <h1>Add Vendor</h1>
    <h2>Basic Path</h2>
    <ol>
      <li><p>The use case begins when the Inventory Manager selects
	  "Add-Vendor"</p></li>
      <li><p>The software prompts for the vendor's name.</p></li>
      <li><p>The software prompts for the vendor's city, state,
	  street, and zipcode.</p></li>
      <li><p>The software prompts for the vendor's phone number.</p></li>
      <li><p>The software prompts for the vendor's fax number.</p></li>
      <li><p>The software prompts for the vendor's website.</p></li>
      <li><p>The software prompts for the vendor's vendor id.</p></li>
      <li><p>The software prompts for alternate vendor id's that
	  are used.</p></li>
      <li><p>The Inventory Manager enters the above prompts.</p></li>
      <li><p>The vendor's address, phone number, fax number, webside,
	     and alternate vendor id's may be left blank.</p></li>
      <li><p>The software checks that the state is a valid US state.</p></li>
      <li><p>The software checks that the phone number is a valid
	  US phone number.</p></li>
      <li><p>The software checks that the webside is a valid website.</p></li>
      <li><p>The software checks that no other vendor has the same
	  vendor id or vendor name.</p></li>
      <li><p>The software adds the vendor.</p></li>
      <li><p>The software updates any listings of vendors.</p></li>
      
      
    <h2>Alternate Paths</h2>
    <h3>DB Error</h3>
